      "es": "",
      "en": "Convert to a string, using engineering notation if an exponent is needed. Engineering notation has an exponent which is a multiple of 3. This can leave up to 3 digits to the left of the decimal place and may require the addition of either one or two trailing zeros. For example, this converts Decimal('123E+1') to Decimal('1.23E+3')."
